<TITLE> Dancing Inmates perform Jackson song </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 PHILLIPINE, Jan 26 (bdnews24.com/Reuters)--- The Dancing Inmates are back with moves from "Michael Jackson's This Is It". The "Dancing Inmates" from a prison in The Philippines, whose rendition of the Michael Jackson hit "Thriller" became a youtube sensation in 2007, are back with a new set of moves paying homage to the late entertainer. The inmates' newest video consists of performances from "Michael Jackson's This Is It," the behind the scenes documentary film on what was to be Jackson's final concert series. Jackson's long-time choreographer Travis Payne, together with two of his back-up dancers, taught the some 1500 inmates from Cebu Provincial Detention and Rehabilitation Center over three days for the event. The video is now on youtube.com in conjunction with DVD release of "Michael Jackson's This Is It" on January
